            <fr:title text="core of an \infty -category">core of an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\infty ]]></fr:tex>-category</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Given a <fr:link href="/forest/htt-0001/" title="\infty -category" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-0001/" display-uri="htt-0001" type="local"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\infty ]]></fr:tex>-category</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, the sub-simplicial set with the same objects, only <fr:link href="/forest/htt-0005/" title="equivalence arrow in an \infty -category" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-0005/" display-uri="htt-0005" type="local">equivalences</fr:link> as edges and all valid higher simplices is called the <html:strong>core</html:strong> of the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\infty ]]></fr:tex>-category, denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {core}(X)]]></fr:tex>. This is an <fr:link href="/forest/htt-0007/" title="\infty -groupoid" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-0007/" display-uri="htt-0007" type="local"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\infty ]]></fr:tex>-groupoid</fr:link>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
